claim.claim-text:
1. A magnetic tape cartridge comprising: 
a cartridge case with a tape leader opening in side walls; 
a single reel having magnetic tape wound thereon, and rotatably housed within said cartridge case; and 
a slide door, which is urged toward a closing position by a spring and held in said closing position by abutting said cartridge case, for opening and closing said tape leader opening; 
wherein said slide door has an abutting surface that abuts said cartridge case, said abutting surface being provided at a position spaced rearward from a front end of said slide door.

3. A magnetic tape cartridge comprising: 
a cartridge case with a tape leader opening in side walls; 
a single reel having magnetic tape wound thereon, and rotatably housed within said cartridge case; and 
a slide door, which is urged toward a closing position by a spring and held in said closing position by abutting said cartridge case, for opening and closing said tape leader opening; 
wherein said cartridge further comprises means for positioning said slide door in said closing position and means for regulating a vertical position of said slide door.

7. A magnetic tape cartridge comprising: 
a cartridge case, formed by fastening upper and lower cases integrally, and having a tape leader opening in side walls of said upper and lower cases; 
a single reel having magnetic tape wound thereon, and rotatably housed within said cartridge case; and 
a slender leader pin firmly attached to a leading end of said magnetic tape and detachably held near said tape leader opening and between said upper and lower cases; 
wherein a small-diameter pin for fastening said upper and lower cases is press-fitted near a holding portion of said cartridge case which holds said leader pin.

9. A magnetic tape cartridge comprising: 
a cartridge case, formed by fastening upper and lower cases integrally, and having a tape leader opening in side walls of said upper and lower cases; 
a single reel having magnetic tape wound thereon, and rotatably housed within said cartridge case; and 
a flat non-contact type memory element, where data is stored, housed within said cartridge case; 
wherein said cartridge case is provided with an element mounting portion having an insertion slit open to a case surface, and after assembly of said cartridge case, said memory element is inserted through said insertion slit and held in said element mounting portion.
